cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is about unsupervised domain adaptation for visual object recognition using deep learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new model called Deep Reconstruction-Classification Network (DRCN), which involves joint learning of a shared encoding representation for two tasks. This suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper uses backpropagation for optimization, which is a common technique in neural networks, indicating that it may also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of DRCN on cross-domain object recognition tasks, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
